<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="317" pageId="13" pageNumber="316" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="316">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="317" pageId="13" pageNumber="316">
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="18" pageNumber="321" refId="B12" refString="Linnavuori, R, 1978. Revision of the African Cicadellidae (subfamilies Nioniinae, Signoretiinae and Drabescinae) (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Annales Entomologici Fennici 44: 33-48." title="Revision of the African Cicadellidae (subfamilies Nioniinae, Signoretiinae and Drabescinae) (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Annales Entomologici Fennici 44: 33 - 48." year="1978">Linnavuori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
included this species in his key and provided illustrations of the male genitalia, but did not include a formal description or list of material examined. However, his figure captions indicate that he examined specimens from the Democratic Republic of Congo (Dingila and Mongbawu). The species is considered 
<pageBreakToken pageId="14" pageNumber="317" start="start">valid</pageBreakToken>
because 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="18" pageNumber="321" refId="B12" refString="Linnavuori, R, 1978. Revision of the African Cicadellidae (subfamilies Nioniinae, Signoretiinae and Drabescinae) (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Annales Entomologici Fennici 44: 33-48." title="Revision of the African Cicadellidae (subfamilies Nioniinae, Signoretiinae and Drabescinae) (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Annales Entomologici Fennici 44: 33 - 48." year="1978">Linnavuori (1978)</bibRefCitation>
satisfied the criteria of availability by including the species in his identification key for African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Signoretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="317">Signoretia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and providing illustrations of features that distinguish the species from its congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
